<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100802842747603></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100802842747603><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=13&mid=100802842747603>Enchanters Rule!</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=13&mid=100802842747603#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=111700><span id= >dilenne</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>5 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Dec 10th 6:53 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>OK, finally going to post something since I feel I have something to add, I hope someone will find this useful.<br><br>First off, Enchanters Rule!  I've never seen an incomplete group refuse to have an Enchanter after Level 20.  NEVER!  Yes in the beginning, before lvl 20, you don't have that much to offer a group; after you get AoE Mezz, and Breeze and Quicken, everyone wants you.<br><br>Next:  While I hear a lot about Breeze, Clarity, C2, etc.  I see very little mentioned about Quicken, Alacrity, and Augmentation.  Those are like Breeze for the tanks in your group.  As soon as you get Quicken start using it on the tanks and get them to tell you when it wears off.  You will make lots of Tank friends that way, and TANKS are your friend!  They will need you as much as you need them.  <br><br>I love my pet for incomplete or small groups.  If I'm in a group of fewer than 4 people, I almost always bring up a pet.  Pets are great tanks, use Rune on yourself, have the puller pull towards you, cast Tash before the mob gets to the rest of the group; the mob will hit you once, after he hits you back off let pet attack, and get back into Caster/support role.<br><br>Also, most chanters seem to use Sympathetic Aura for buying stuff only.  Use it when fighting Evil Eyes or other Enchanter class mob's.  Help keep your tanks on your side.  Higher Charisma helps to resist charm spells, give it to your group too, and ALWAYS keep SA on yourself.  <br><br>Many posts have mentioned this, but I'll give my 2cents worth.  Always give Clerics, Wizards and Druids; Breeze, or Clarity FREE whenever you see them and if Mana permits, with Druids they'll usually SoW you right then!  I never pay for ports, SoW's or Heals. Why?  Because I never charge for Clarity and just about everyone knows it.  Just shout &quot;Trade Clarity for SoW&quot; and typically they will come to you.  Will I take a donation, of course, jewel craft is expensive.  But I don't request a donation unless I know the person is a crack-head beggar.<br><br>I made a mistake making my chanter a follower of Mithaniel Marr, so far it hasn't hurt me too much, though it has been limiting.  Benevolence helps, but if I had it to do over, I would make an agnostic Enchanter.<br><br>Don't bother with Concordance of Research, but do let EVERYONE you meet know that you need &quot;pages&quot;, torn pages, tomes, etc.  Anything with a page number.  You'll get enough from people who know that they will want to be your friend in the future.  Keep Runes for Wizzies and Words for Necros.  Give these away if the person can use them.  In return they will usually give you pages to use for research.<br><br>Favorite hunting spot after lvl 20- Beholders Maze and Evil Eyes.  Bring a Wizzie, Paladin or Cleric with you.  At first it'll be hard but the loot is good and so is xp.  Be careful of Lord Soptyvr and kill eyes before they can bring up a pet if you can.  Hide behind the pillar on the right side and make sure you go in invisible if you can.  At lvl 20 or so, I'd recommend a group of 4 or more, and you won't regret it.  Polished Bone Bracelets, gems and generally 1 to 5 pp per eye that you kill, and  minos give fair loot too.<br><br>Finally:  Use your illusions.  Troll form gives you regen, skelly form is just too cool.  Later you get Air elemental, free lev. And they are just too cool to play with.  Be careful though remember illusions will make you KOS with guards and other NPC's.  I had an Aviak vendor kill me when I played with Troll form in front of him.  I found it mildly amusing and embarassing at the time.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
